description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The newly established Vaccine and Testing research team at UHBW are looking for enthusiastic and motivated nurses and clinical research practitioners to join the team!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Vaccine and Testing research team will lead on supporting Principal Investigators in the setup and delivery of vaccine and testing research, including and prioritising COVID-19 research and other urgent public health studies. The research will be based at the Clinical Research and Imaging Centre, a purpose built clinical research facility which offers the ability to conduct early and late phase studies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are recruiting Band 5 research nurses and clinical research practitioners who will support the research sister in the safe and effective delivery of these critical studies whilst also acting as a resource for staff, researchers, research participants and patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must possess a keen interest in research, have excellent communication skills and be able to work well within a multi-disciplinary team. You will take a proactive approach in supporting clinical research studies including supporting the consent process, undertaking participant assessments and sampling procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role requires close working with colleagues across the trust and with all clinical divisions, therefore excellent communication and interpersonal skills are a must.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we can offer you a friendly working environment with professional support and training/development opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will consider both full or part time hours, please indicate your preference on your application&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKelly TurnerJob titleResearch Sister: Vaccine &amp; Testing TeamEmail addresskelly.turner@uhbw.nhs.ukTelephone number01173420589Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
